[normal]DEVELOPMENTS SINCE JULY[bold] 2013[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the 
[normal]publication in July of 
[normal]the Government’s 
[normal]response to the public 
[normal]consultation o
[normal]n Schedule 7 which I had recommended in my 2011 report and which was conducted in
[normal] late 2012
[normal], attracting 395 responses
[normal];
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the detention in August of David Miranda under Schedule 7 at Heathrow, giving rise to a storm of 
[normal]media 
[normal]controversy and a 
[normal]c
[normal]laim for judicial review
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]not yet decided, which raised a number of issues including 
[normal]the scope of the Schedule 7 power and its use in relation to 
[normal]what is said by Mr Miranda to be journalistic material
[normal];
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the rejection in August by the Divisional C
[normal]ourt of a claim by a French national
[normal], examined at Heathrow, that 
[normal]the application of 
[normal]Schedule 7 contravened Articles 5, 6 and 8 of the ECHR
[normal] and EU free movement rules
[normal];
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](d)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a Liberal Democrat conference motion 
[normal]in October, 
[normal]calling for further safeguards;
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](e)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the publication in October of an “
[normal]illustrative
[normal]” draft revised Code of Practice
[normal] for examining officers
[normal];
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](f)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]a report
[normal] in October by the Joint Committee of Human Rights, making a number of recommendations for the further reform of Schedule 7;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](g)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a
[normal] 
[normal]Supreme Court 
[normal]dictum
[normal] in October
[normal], in a judgment written by its President and the recently-retired Lord Chief Justice
[normal] and concurred in by five other Justices
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]expressing concern 
[normal]about the breadth of the powers given to ports officers by Schedule 7;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](h)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the grant in November of a declaration that the refusal of police officers to await the arrival of a solicitor requested by a person detained under Schedule 7 before putting further questions to him was unlawful
[normal];
[normal] and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](i)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
